modules.description: This module provides functions to apply color formatting to strings using ANSI escape codes. It includes specific functions to paint strings red or cyan, and appends a reset signal to terminate color formatting. The module works directly with string values and a predefined list of color-escape code pairs.

This module provides operations to retrieve the current version of ocamlformat, obtain preset configuration settings, and write those settings to a file. It works with string data types to represent version numbers and configuration content. A concrete use case is generating a default configuration file for ocamlformat in a project setup.

This module applies color formatting to strings using ANSI escape codes and retrieves ocamlformat version and configuration presets. It works with strings and predefined color mappings, supporting use cases like highlighting terminal output and generating default configuration files. Specific functions include painting strings red or cyan, and writing configuration data to disk.
